We should try to avoid the message service as much as possible for asking the user for confirmation. I suggest to open a real dialog after the user clicks on "Uninstall" instead of using message service.

We do the very same for all other UX interactions that require confirmation (e.g. deleting a file, undoing all changes).

@sandy081 can we do this for October?

- VSCode Version: 1.6.1

When editing a .less file unexpected errors show when working with mixins. These errors show when using a mixin with an empty parameter.
- Code :

``` less
.mixin(@color; @padding: 2) {
  color: @color;
  padding: @padding;
}

.some .selector div {
  .mixin(#008000;);
}
```
